  "local_port": 51696,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can you locate the name of a proxy server?",
  "response": "To locate the name of a proxy server, you can follow several steps:\n\n1. **Check Browser Settings:** \n   - **Chrome:** Go to `Settings -> Advanced -> System -> Open your computer's proxy settings`. This will show the proxy settings of your operating system (OS).\n   - **Firefox:** Go to `Options -> General -> Network Settings -> Settings`. Here you can see the proxy settings used by Firefox.\n   - **Edge:** Go to `Settings -> System -> Open your computer's proxy settings`.\n\n2. **Operating System Settings:**\n   - **Windows:** \n     - Open `Control Panel -> Internet Options -> Connections -> LAN Settings`. Proxy details will be listed here if they are configured.\n   - **Mac:** \n     - Go to `System Preferences -> Network -> Advanced -> Proxies`. Here, you can find the proxy configurations.\n\n3. **Network Settings:**\n   - **Command Prompt (Windows):**\n     - Open Command Prompt and type `netsh winhttp show proxy`. This command displays the proxy server settings.\n   - **Terminal (Linux/Mac):**\n     - Type `env | grep -i proxy`. This will show any environment variables related to proxy settings.\n     - In some distributions, checking `/etc/environment` or `/etc/apt/apt.conf.d/` may also reveal proxy details.\n\n4. **Applications Configurations:**\n   - Some applications may have their own proxy settings within their configuration menus.\n\n5. **Manual Configuration:**\n   - Sometimes, proxy settings might be manually configured in configuration files like `.bashrc`, `.profile`, or specific application configuration files.\n\n6. **Network Administrator:**\n   - If the proxy server is set up by your organization, the network administrator should be able to provide you with the proxy server name and settings.\n\n7. **Proxy Software:**\n   - If you are using proxy software like Squid or similar, check their respective configurations or documentation.\n\nKnowing these methods, you can locate and identify proxy server names and settings in different environments.",
